			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				
				<strong>Fuck Gary Bettman -- a hockey rant</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#330066" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>Wow, just typing the title for this post makes me feel better.  <br />
<br />
I don't know where to start on this, but I do know that I'd run NHL chief Gary Bettman down like a dog in the street given the opportunity.  The man that brought us the Mighty Ducks of Anaheim (the stuffed Simba doll of the NHL), is busy salting the fields of NHL hockey.  <br />
<br />
The NHL Players Association (NHLPA) recently offered a new proposal for resolving the current stand-off between the players union and the NHL.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.nhlpa.com/Content/Feature.asp?contentId=3398" target="_blank">NHLPA Proposal</a> <br />
<br />
Among other items, the NHLPA proposal includes an immediate 24% reduction in player salaries and a so-called luxury tax on teams who exceed a set player payroll level ($45 million).  This is a huge step by the players, which is on the verge of being dismissed out of hand by Bettman because it doesn't include a set salary cap.  <br />
<br />
Well,  I say fuck him.  If the owners are too stupid to set and meet payroll budgets, then they deserve to drive the NHL into oblivion.  Shit, the guys at NASCAR are probably laughing their asses off at the ineptitude of the guys running the NHL.  <br />
<br />
This season is almost assuredly dead and I'm not sure next year looks much better.  The owners say they lose less money by not playing the season.  To which I say:  not if you count the damage being done to the long-term viability of the league.  I don't know for sure what happens when a sports league goes bust, but I'm pretty sure franchise values approach zero.  If that seems like a good deal to owners, then they can keep saving money by not playing the games.  Fuck you too.<br />
<br />
Give me Hockey Night in Sweden, complete with the Swedish version of Don fucking Cherry.  (OK, there probably isn't a Swedish version of Don Cherry, but maybe they can import someone.)<br />
<br />
Live from Oslo &lt;ESPN_hockey_music&gt; National Hockey Night! &lt;/ESPN_hockey_music&gt; Tonight, Peter Forsberg leads Modo against Frolunda . . .<br />
<br />
Drop the fucking puck already!<br />
<br />
Gentex</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
