<br />
Amen Brother!<br />
<br />
As far as salaries go, yes, they are out of line with what revenues will support.  It's only gotten that way because a fair number of the owners are dipshits who believed Bettman when he told them the NHL was the second coming of the NBA.  They projected revenues (TV revenues primarily) and thus salaries that were out of line with reality.  The fact that they contracted to pay players based on Bettman's fantasy is the problem, not that players agreed to rich contracts.  <br />
<br />
The players have made a good faith proposal to cut salaries drastically.  The owners need to come to the table with something more than piss-off until you agree to a salary cap.<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px; ">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>Originally Posted by <strong>Donis</strong></div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Hockey doesn't generate revenue like football, baseball or even the better basketball markets and until the NHLPA bites the bullet - there won't be a season. Oh - don't kid yourself - The owners will just dissolve the NHL and form another league if things degenerate much further. Then the players will have to worry about more than a cap.</div>
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div> <br />
<br />
I don't really disagree Donis.  NHL players cannot be paid like NBA or NFL players because the money just isn't there.  However, I disagree with the idea that the owners can simply disolve the NHL and start over.  They have a lot of money invested in the NHL brand and the individual brands of their teams.  They risk flushing all of that down the toilet if they can't come to an agreement.  <br />
<br />
Who would you rather watch play:<br />
<br />
The best players in the world in generic uniforms,<br />
<br />
or<br />
<br />
A buch of stiffs from the local beer-league decked out in the nicest NHL uniforms?<br />
<br />
The players are the game in my mind.  There is no substitute for what guys like Lemieux or Sakic (or any of the great players) can do with a stick and a little rubber disk.  My beloved Red Wings logo is just a stupid tire with feathers on it without Gordie Howe, Steve Yzerman and Sergei Fedorov.  Sure, the organisation of the NHL has allowed the players to get rich, but it's the players that make people pay to watch.<br />
<br />
Gentex</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
