<!-- open content container -->

	<div align="center">
		<div class="page" style="width:100%; text-align:left">
			<div style="padding:0px 25px 0px 25px">
<div style="padding:0px 0px 6px 0px">

<table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
<tr>
	<td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" >		
			<!-- status icon and date -->
			<a name="post568667"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/statusicon/post_old.gif" alt="Old" border="0" /></a>
			
				December 14th, 2004, 04:32 PM
			
			
			<!-- / status icon and date -->				
	</td>
	<td class="thead" style="font-weight:normal" align="right">
		&nbsp;
		

		 #<a href="showpost.php?s=de327bf8768344734e1e8be8e916937c&amp;p=568667&amp;postcount=13" target="new"><strong>13</strong></a>
	</td>
</tr>
<tr valign="top">
	<td class="alt2" width="175">
			
			<div id="postmenu_568667">
				<a class="bigusername" href="member.php?s=de327bf8768344734e1e8be8e916937c&amp;u=994">Delores Mulva</a>
				<script type="text/javascript"> vbmenu_register("postmenu_568667", true); </script>
			</div>
                        


			<div class="smallfont">Forum Channeler</div>
			
			
			<!-- Avatars -->		
			
			<!-- /Avatars -->
			<div class="smallfont">
<br>



<br />
<div>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131561" target="blank">Magelo Profile</a></div>

</div>
				
				<div>
					
					
				</div>
				<div>   </div>
			</div>					
		
	</td>
	<td class="alt1">
	
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>There's two types of owners. Type one has very deep pockets, and regards their team as a bit of an ego trip. They will pay unrealistic salaries (which will become the &quot;comparables&quot; for the next round of salary negotiations) to get the bragging rights that go with a winning team. Type two does not have deep pockets, and has to run their team as a business to stay in the league. In the long term, the only way the two can coexist and be competitive is with a salary cap or equivalent.<br />
<br />
The players don't care about that. They don't mind teams being uncompetitive, or teams folding just to be bought and moved by someone else. Their concern is with their wages, and those will be brought down significantly by a cap. They also don't trust the owners, who have been known to hide hockey-related revenue in other companies (such as the holding companies for the stadiums) to make things look worse than they really are. The NHLPA offer doesn't do anything to offer long-term stability to the league, so it is at best a temporary solution.<br />
<br />
Having said that, I blame the ownership group for prolonging this mess. A severe luxury tax is an effective salary cap. No owner is going to pay $99 per $1 over the luxury threshold, or $100 million total for every $1 million they wish to exceed the threshold by, for an example of how to engineer an effective cap. So clinging to a cap structure is not necessary, and rejecting the union's offer without a counter-offer is highly counter-productive to resolving the lockout. Offer the same thing with a massive luxury tax, work from there. If they can't find middle ground within that framework so be it, but at least TRY to negotiate!<br />
<br />
I also blame the NHL for bailing out bankrupt franchises. Had the NHL let bankrupt franchises disappear, and made the players on those teams unrestricted free agents (as opposed to a dispersal draft), the players would have seen that high contracts could lead to a reduction in the number of jobs available to players. As it is now, they know that the league will bail out any franchise in trouble until a new owner with deeper pockets can be found.<br />
<br />
I don't think we'll have hockey this year. I have doubts about hockey starting on time next year. And most disturbingly, I, a season ticket holder for the Canucks for decades, am starting to not care if they come back or not.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
	</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td class="alt2">
		<img class="inlineimg" src="images/statusicon/user_offline.gif" alt="Delores Mulva is offline" border="0" />


		
		
		
		&nbsp;
	</td>
