		<div>The players are at fault this time. The NHL simply cannot survive without a salary cap. Both the NFL and NBA have it, and the other sport that doesn't have it and shall remain nameless, has players on some teams earning more then a whole team on a small market team. The NHL does not have the TV revenue in the US to maintain current salaries. Salaries in the NHL are higher then the NFL; that is not sound business.<br />
